                <div class="jonra" data-uuid="28c6ef7dde21491886c0777b7f3e58bc">
                    <h2 data-uuid="7771d8f113564196aed63402fed215d5"><b><i>Democracy in America</i></b></h2>
                    <p class="source" data-uuid="fc2b6eb3fccc4971a18bef2eae28a813">When Alexis de Tocqueville of France visited the United States in the early 1830s, he identified what he called a very American quality.</p>
                </div>
                <section class="historical-source-image-text-audio" data-uuid="271a3914a9864d8f93c2762becdc15da">
                    <section class="pullquote_wrapper" data-uuid="5ab85571c30e46898368e95b4cb5d8cb">
                        <p class="pullquote hang" data-uuid="081204baa27041bc9116925c7bfddd44">“[Americans want] to be always making life more comfortable and convenient, to avoid trouble, and to satisfy the smallest wants [desires] without effort and almost without cost.”</p>
                        <div class="pullquote_attribution_wrapper" data-uuid="0d57088388c94ff49150f726712e8124">
